sect1.para:
With the increasing popularity of graphical desktop systems, the use of graphical e-mail programs like GNOME's evolution, KDE's kmail or Mozilla's thunderbird (in &debian; available as icedove
The reason that thunderbird has been renamed to icedove in &debian; has to do with licensing issues. Details are outside the scope of this manual.
) is becoming more popular. These programs combine the function of a MUA, MTA and MDA, but can — and often are — also be used in combination with the traditional Linux tools.
